    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> The user can simply add a css class to the container element to style the inner select\n\nWe do have it in some other places (like the searchBox), mostly because sometimes (like when using bootstrap), adding a class on the wrapper element does not allows you to style your form element accordingly.\n\nIf you find a way on the API side to provide a full template then maybe it would solve the `cssClass` thing\n",
