  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> We need a better name than indexSelector because what we are really providing is a sort results widget.\n> What about `sortOrderSelector` for this widget name?\n\nI've been thinking about it and:\n- the sorting is really not a UI thing with Algolia: it appears very confusing to me to have a \"sort\" widget because what this widget will do is update the targeted index and will not deal at all with sorts\n- I'm not sure we need to make it display the \"Sort by:\" label\n\nAt the end it's really an `indexSelector` and the user is free to use it to configure the sort orders if he built the slaves to do it.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-09-04T09:49:57Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/38#issuecomment-137692656",
